snippet.textDisplay: We have one of these at work, but the slightly older one back when they still used CAT engines. We bought it to tow a big trailer that carries our race cars and still have the crew fit comfortably when driving across the country. The CAT engines are wayyy more powerful than the ford engines. I also know many people that own these that work at horse farms and use them to get to horse shows, again to fit the family comfortably while being able to tow a massive camper or horse trailer. These are not generally bought by someone just to flex, they’re actually used for work.

These are called SuperCrewzer. Ford has been making these since 2000 for ranchers and equestrian sporters, not Californians.

I own a 2002 F750 Lariat setup just like this to pull our 45’ horse trailer. The insurance is much cheaper than a passenger van and don’t have to deal with CDL regulations.

You feeling like the king of the road driving this, sounds like you’re projecting some deeply rooted insecurities. My 2010 Kenworth W900L surpasses my 02 F750 by 60k lbs on a cold day.
